Privacy Policy
​Dear users, thank you for choosing our application.We take your privacy very seriously.This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information.The terms in this Privacy Policy are consistent with our Terms and Conditions, which can be consulted within the application unless specifically defined herein.
​​1.How and Why We Collect Your Data
​We collect data to provide and improve our services.This section explains the types of information we collect and the purposes for which we use it.
​-Location Information: We do not collect your location information.  However, third parties such as Google, Facebook, and Adjust may collect your approximate location for analytics and advertising purposes.
-Personal Information: We do not collect your email, SMS, MMS, or other in-app information.
-Photos and Videos: We collect and store the photos you upload (including facial photos) for local style adjustment or modification through AI models deployed on our servers.This data is stored solely on Amazon's data storage in California, USA, and is not shared with any third party. We only retain stylized or partially modified data.
-Audio Files: We do not collect your voice, recordings, or other audio files.
-Files: We do not collect your files or documents.
-Calendar Information: We do not collect or share your calendar information.
-Contacts: We do not collect contact information you share with us.
-App Activity: We do not collect or share your app interactions, in-app search history, or other behavioral data.
-Web Browsing: We do not collect or share your web browsing history.
-Application Information and Performance: We collect crash logs, diagnostic information, etc., to improve system stability and service quality.
-Device ID or Other ID: We collect this information for personalization and analysis and share it with third parties.
2.Protecting Your Information
​-We process personal data and sensitive user data securely, using the latest encryption technologies (such as HTTPS) to transmit data and runtime permission requests before accessing data controlled by device permissions.
-We ensure the security of personal data and sensitive user data.We also require vendors who process personal information on our behalf to take appropriate security measures and provide users with means to delete their data.
-Data is stored for a maximum of 90 days, after which it is automatically deleted.
​3.Your Rights
​If you live in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, you have certain rights under applicable law.Please contact us to exercise your rights and be prepared to verify your identity.Note that your rights may be limited in certain circumstances.
​​4.Third-Party Privacy Policies
​Our products and services involve working with third parties.You can find links to their privacy policies below.These policies are administered by third parties and are not under our control.
https://www.adjust.com/terms/privacy-policy/
https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy
​​5.Children's Privacy
​Our products and services are not intended for children under the age of 13.We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13.If a child under 13 provides personal information, we will immediately delete that information from our servers.
​​6.Policy Changes
​We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time.By continuing to use our services after these changes are made, you accept the updated policy.
